"{\"uid\": \"catholicculture.org-commentary-lukewarm-vatican-response-to-paris-olympic-outrage\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Prayer with Wings: 2025 Fall CampaignHelp us raise$125,000tolift our mission higher!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 84, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By Phil Lawler(bio-articles-email) | Aug 05, 2024    What's wrong withthe Vatican statement on the Olympic blasphemy?\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nearly everything.\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Start with the timing.\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than a week passed between the opening ceremonies of the Paris Olympics and the release of the tepid Vatican response.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"During that week thousands of people had expressed their shock and anger over a deliberate insult to the Blessed Sacrament-the source and summit of the Catholic faith.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 523, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3633638319909903e-14, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So the world naturally turned to Rome for an authoritative response, and for several days heard-nothing at all.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 650, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"score\": 0.9999992052292758, \"rank\": 7.944563992503691e-07, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then when the Vatican did release a short statement, it was vouchsafed to the world on a Saturday afternoon.\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is the time usually chosen by publicists who feel obliged to put something on the record, but donotwant to capture public attention-the time to \\\"bury\\\" a news story.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A reasonably strong statement, at that point, might have been categorized as \\\"too little, too late.\\\"\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But this was not a strong statement.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Holy See was saddened\\\" is began.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Saddened?\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Are we only \\\"saddened\\\" by public mockery of someone we love?\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact the Vatican (deliberately?)\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"missed the essential point.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement went on to \\\"deplore the offense caused to many Christians and believers of other religions,\\\" and later referred to \\\"allusions ridiculing the religious convictions of many people.\\\"\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1305, \"end\": 1315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9940371136352384, \"rank\": 0.00569744309140708, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show in question had not included a few \\\"allusions\\\" that mocked religion; it was a sustained attack.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More important, the show was not merely an offense against Christians; it was an offense against God.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9940371136352384, \"rank\": 0.00569744309140708, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What the Vatican handled as a breach of good manners was in facta deliberate blasphemy, a violation of God's first commandment.\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be sure, there were other reasons to be disgusted by the Olympic opening ceremonies.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Secular commentators could, and did, deplore the offense against ordinary civility, and on the limits of free speech in a healthy society.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 2001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the world expects the Holy See to see events through the eyes of faith.\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2077, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"score\": 0.9999992275669028, \"rank\": 7.724333125425131e-07, \"text\": \"Holy See\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From that perspective the sin of blasphemy is far more serious than the hurt feelings of believers.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Late last week both the president of Turkey and the government of Iran hadurged Pope Francis to speak out.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.626562221335759, \"rank\": 0.5960106848897252, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 2245, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.999960120677618, \"rank\": 2.357975667801911e-05, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 2259, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The timing of the tardy Vatican statement raises the question: Was the Vatican more concerned about the reaction of Muslim leaders than the outrage among the world's faithful Catholics?\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2402, \"end\": 2408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9996389930958831, \"rank\": 0.00036113727731243043, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9835837865106122e-16, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even after a direct plea from Turkey's President Erdogan, Pope Francis still has not issued his own statement.\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2503, \"end\": 2509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.626562221335759, \"rank\": 0.5960106848897252, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\", \"score\": 0.9996957007693985, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erdogan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\"}, {\"begin\": 2531, \"end\": 2543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Presumably the unsigned statement from the Holy See could not have been issued without his approval.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2627, \"end\": 2635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"score\": 0.9999992275669028, \"rank\": 7.724333125425131e-07, \"text\": \"Holy See\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still the fact remains that an insult to our Lord Jesus in the Eucharist has been met with silence from his Vicar in Rome.\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2735, \"end\": 2740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999995346776077, \"rank\": 4.6532281865006924e-07, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2748, \"end\": 2757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 0.9999999692927308, \"rank\": 3.070733347346514e-08, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}, {\"begin\": 2793, \"end\": 2798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vicar\", \"score\": 0.9999272421222379, \"rank\": 7.27631712113925e-05, \"text\": \"Vicar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vicar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vicar\"}, {\"begin\": 2802, \"end\": 2806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"score\": 0.9999992052292758, \"rank\": 7.944563992503691e-07, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How can we explain the Pope's silence on this Paris outrage?\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2855, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999992410267, \"rank\": 7.588585019863125e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps it is part of a pattern.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bear in mind that Pope Francis has not celebrated Mass in public himself for more than two years now.\", \"from\": 2903, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2921, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Pope often \\\"presides\\\" at Mass, and delivers homilies, but he has not acted as principal celebrant of the Eucharistic liturgy.\", \"from\": 3005, \"to\": 3134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3114, \"end\": 3133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_(liturgy)\", \"score\": 0.9999999990095603, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eucharistic liturgy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_(liturgy)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mass_(liturgy)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it a question of priorities?\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If so, what could be more important for the Supreme Pontiff-the \\\"High Priest\\\" of the Catholic Church-than the Eucharist?\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3252, \"end\": 3260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3633638319909903e-14, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 3277, \"end\": 3286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 0.9999999692927308, \"rank\": 3.070733347346514e-08, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phil Lawlerhas been a Catholic journalist for more than 30 years.\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3313, \"end\": 3321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3633638319909903e-14, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has edited several Catholic magazines and written eight books.\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3379, \"end\": 3387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3633638319909903e-14, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Founder of Catholic World News, he is the news director and lead analyst at CatholicCulture.org.See full bio.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All comments are moderated.\", \"from\": 3534, \"to\": 3561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To lighten our editing burden, only current donors are allowed to Sound Off.\", \"from\": 3562, \"to\": 3638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are a current donor,log into see the comment form; otherwise pleasesupport our work, and Sound Off!\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3735, \"end\": 3744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sound_Off_(film)\", \"score\": 0.8311509410018365, \"rank\": 0.14062499999999775, \"text\": \"Sound Off\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sound_Off_(film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sound_Off_(film)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A measured column on the feckless and weak response of the Vatican and the continued non-response of the Holy Father Jorg\\u00e9 B\\u2026 The curious fact that HFJB Will not celebrate mass except as a concelebrant might cause one to wonder about either his health or his priestly commitment to the sacraments of the Church.\", \"from\": 3747, \"to\": 4058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks you for continuing to reflect on this curious and disturbing fact about HFJ.\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Retired01 has it right.\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A commentator referred to the Pope as washing his hands like Pontius Pilate so as not to offend with any critical statement his earthly overlords.\", \"from\": 4168, \"to\": 4314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4229, \"end\": 4243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontius_Pilate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0753154840622763e-55, \"text\": \"Pontius Pilate\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontius_Pilate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontius_Pilate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the top?\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadly for this Pope I do not think so not to mention his public support for the whole LGBTQ etc ideology in league with Fr James Martin.\", \"from\": 4331, \"to\": 4467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4460, \"end\": 4466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999999990700417, \"rank\": 9.247034832444336e-10, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This type of blasphemy that occurred in Paris is a constant theme in public manifestations of what they call \\\"queer culture\\\" Mockery with mimicry of divine things is a sign of the diabolical.\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4509, \"end\": 4514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999992410267, \"rank\": 7.588585019863125e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, sorry but this is great and good news.\", \"from\": 4662, \"to\": 4706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had no idea my sins were merely violations of good manners.\", \"from\": 4707, \"to\": 4768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The bad news is it puts me in the chimeric crosshairs of secular whims that continually float convenient redefinitions of \\\"good manners.\\\"\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Pope's belated, tepid, milquetoast response to the blasphemy was itself blasphemous.\", \"from\": 4908, \"to\": 4996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heartsickening.\", \"from\": 4997, \"to\": 5012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's amazing that the president of Turkey and the government of Iran both urged Pope Francis to speak out.\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5049, \"end\": 5055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.626562221335759, \"rank\": 0.5960106848897252, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 5078, \"end\": 5082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.999960120677618, \"rank\": 2.357975667801911e-05, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 5094, \"end\": 5106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not know that.\", \"from\": 5121, \"to\": 5141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the west's most bitter enemies...figuratively begging the west to save itself.\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Absolutely amazing.\", \"from\": 5228, \"to\": 5247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What a shame that they are more offended by blasphemy than the Pope.\", \"from\": 5248, \"to\": 5316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the reason for the late and lukewarm response is concern about not offending the LGBT party.\", \"from\": 5318, \"to\": 5418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5407, \"end\": 5411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9998668159714057, \"rank\": 0.0001226329507217438, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today the Roman Martyrology commemorates St. Bibiana (died c. 361) who was martyred at Rome under Julian the Apostate around the year 361.\", \"from\": 5420, \"to\": 5558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5430, \"end\": 5447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Martyrology\", \"score\": 0.9999291835525934, \"rank\": 7.082146273756209e-05, \"text\": \"Roman Martyrology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Martyrology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Martyrology\"}, {\"begin\": 5465, \"end\": 5472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Bibiana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.520016184357711e-22, \"text\": \"Bibiana\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Bibiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Bibiana\"}, {\"begin\": 5507, \"end\": 5511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"score\": 0.9999992052292758, \"rank\": 7.944563992503691e-07, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Church also commemorates St. Silverius (480-537), who was pope for a very short time in 546-7 A.D.\", \"from\": 5563, \"to\": 5665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5596, \"end\": 5605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Silverius\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Silverius\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Silverius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Silverius\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But his brief pontificate made him a\\u2026  Learn more about this day.\", \"from\": 5666, \"to\": 5731, \"entities\": []}]}"